Bring a large #pot{} of water to a boil with a large pinch of @salt{}. Meanwhile, quarter the @zucchini{1}(quartered lengthwise), then cut into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Halve, peel, and finely dice the @red onion{1}(finely diced). Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Cut half the @lemon{1} into wedges. Remove the @Sweet Italian pork sausage{6%ounce} from its casing.

Heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a pan over medium-high heat. Add the sausage and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up the pieces, for about ~{6%minutes}, until golden brown. Set aside.

Add the onions and zucchini to the same pan and season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and as many @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} as you dare (we used 1⁄4 teaspoon). Cook over medium heat for about ~{5%minutes}, until onions have softened and zucchini is browned. Add the garlic and @dried thyme{1%teaspoon} and cook for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant.

Add the @linguine{6%ounce} to the boiling water and cook for ~{9-10%minutes}, until al dente.

Add the sausage and the @diced tomatoes{1%can} and season with @pepper{}. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer while the pasta cooks.

Once cooked, drain and add the linguine to the pan with the sauce. Toss to combine and finish with a squeeze of the half lemon.

> Adding the pasta directly to the sauce at the end helps it to absorb all the flavors. Remember, pasta is the vehicle for that delicious sauce!

Serve the pasta in #bowls{} and sprinkle the @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} on top. Serve with lemon wedges on the side!